{"questionId":"17679","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A bar rotates horizontally about its centre, reaching a maximum angular velocity in six complete rotations from rest. The bar has a constant angular acceleration of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>110</mn><mo> </mo><mi>rad</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. The moment of inertia of the bar about the axis of rotation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0216</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f095fbb3301389c048eeda6b6136ae1906af61d2.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Draw the variation with time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> of the angular displacement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> of the bar during the acceleration.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3c63052128945b58c8fb7eb60a8a50a138835945.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">concave up from origin </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">✓</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/c23d39ac7a31bc1158ac3995b69e51cd806d8f98.png\"></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17679","referenceCode":"20N.3.SL.TZ0.6b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw the variation with time t of the angular displacement θ of the bar during the acceleration.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.1 – Rigid bodies and rotational dynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}